ing Botswanan, 21, was one of the standout performers in Paris this year, becoming the first African to win the men's 200m and silver in the 4x400m relay.\", \"from\": 583, \"to\": 837, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 625, \"end\": 631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Betway\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Betway\"}, {\"begin\": 740, \"end\": 745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.235524642234069e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a little magic\", \"from\": 587, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"your every day\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 619}, {\"ngram\": \"a world\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"casino games\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 670}, {\"ngram\": \"The unassuming Botswanan\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 695}, {\"ngram\": \"the standout performers\", \"from\": 712, \"to\": 735}, {\"ngram\": \"the first African\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 200m\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 809, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"the 4x400m relay\", \"from\": 819, \"to\": 835}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Botswana's first Olympic gold medallist in any sport, he ran an African 200m record of 19.46 seconds, placing him fifth on the world all-time list and beating US star Noah Lyles into third place.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 1034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9964654854914724, \"rank\": 0.003523121801583769, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1006, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any sport\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 891}, {\"ngram\": \"an African 200m record\", \"from\": 900, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"19.46 seconds\", \"from\": 926, \"to\": 939}, {\"ngram\": \"the world all-time list\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"third place\", \"from\": 1022, \"to\": 1033}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It came just months after he suffered the trauma of losing his mother, Seratiwa, who died in May - he credits her as being the \\\"powerhouse, the drive\\\" behind his success.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1206, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trauma\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1084}, {\"ngram\": \"his mother\", \"from\": 1095, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"Seratiwa\", \"from\": 1107, \"to\": 1115}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1132}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"powerhouse\", \"from\": 1159, \"to\": 1174}, {\"ngram\": \"the drive\", \"from\": 1176, \"to\": 1185}, {\"ngram\": \"his success\", \"from\": 1194, \"to\": 1205}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a sign of his new-found status, Tebogo is one of two finalists for the men's track athlete of the year award, along with Norway's Jakob Ingebrigtsen.\", \"from\": 1208, \"to\": 1360, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1332, \"end\": 1338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9999936755525501, \"rank\": 4.960519878389012e-06, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 1341, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jakob_Ingebrigtsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jakob Ingebrigtsen\", \"typ